File.encoding 

  <L=51#6> String </L> encoding

Description 

Gets or sets the encoding for subsequent read/write operations.

One of the encoding constants listed in the?JavaScript Tools Guide. If the value is not recognized, uses
the system default encoding.A special encoder, BINARY, is used to read binary files. It stores each byte
of the file as one Unicode character regardless of any encoding. When writing, the lower byte of each
Unicode character is treated as a single byte to write.

