File.readch 

  <L=51#6> String </L> readch ()

Description 

Reads a single text character from the file at the current position.

Line feeds are recognized as CR, LF, CRLF or LFCR pairs. If the file is encoded, multiple bytes might be
read to create a single Unicode character. Returns a string that contains the character.

