Folder.remove 

  bool remove ()

Description 

Deletes the folder associated with this object from disk immediately, without moving it to the system
trash.

Folders must be empty before they can be deleted. Does not resolve aliases; instead, deletes the
referenced alias or shortcut file itself. Returns true if the file was successfully removed. IMPORTANT:
Cannot be undone. It is recommended that you prompt the user for permission before deleting.

