XML.hasSimpleContent 

  bool hasSimpleContent ()

Description 

Reports whether this XML object contains simple content.

An XML object is considered to contain simple content if it represents a text node, represents an
attribute node or if it represents an XML element that has no child elements. XML objects representing
comments and processing instructions do not have simple content. The existence of attributes, comments,
processing instructions and text nodes within an XML object is not significant in determining if it has
simple content.

